The Sheep in the Baðstofa - Final Production Bible v2.0
A 12-Minute Icelandic Horror Film
CRITICAL PRODUCTION PHILOSOPHY
The Three-Layer Reality (Absolute Foundation)
Every frame must support three simultaneous truths, never collapsing to singular explanation:

Physical Reality: Hákarl neurotoxins (trimethylamine oxide), starvation ketosis, hypothermia confusion, ergot contamination in stored grain
Psychological Reality: Dissociative fugue from trauma, folie à famille (shared psychosis), guilt manifestation, collective hysteria from isolation
Supernatural Reality: Tilberi invocation answered literally, forystufé judgment, huldufolk intervention, transformation as escape/punishment

Testing Principle: If a shot definitively proves only one interpretation, rewrite it.
The Action Blindspot Solution (Production Reality)
AI image generation cannot convincingly render:

Complex physical interactions between subjects
Transformation moments or morphing
Precise emotional expressions during action
Multiple subjects interacting dynamically

Our Solution - Show Only:

Aftermath states (swinging lamp, not the strike)
Before/after positions (human face, then sheep face)
Environmental evidence (tracks in snow, scattered wool)
Implied action through sound design

Scale as Narrative Architecture
Camera movement creates meaning:

Cosmic Distance → Divine abandonment
Domestic Compression → Inescapable proximity
Personal Intimacy → Inside the breaking mind
Cosmic Return → Abandoned to consequences

Prompt Engineering Principles

Front-load critical elements: Main subject first, then environment, then details
Use photographic language: "Close-up," "wide shot," "shallow depth of field"
Specify lighting direction: "Lamp light from left," "backlit by window"
Include material textures: "Rough wool," "smooth ice," "weathered wood"
Lock camera angles: "Eye level," "looking up," "45-degree angle"
Add atmospheric particles: "Dust motes," "breath vapor," "smoke wisps"

COMPREHENSIVE ENVIRONMENT ANCHORS
BAÐSTOFA INTERIOR-STANDARD:
"Dark interior of 12x16 foot turf house, single whale oil lamp creating golden light pool with deep shadows beyond, blackened ceiling beams with sheep wool insulation visible between rafters, frost crystallizing on inner turf walls in fractal patterns, grey-pink shark meat hanging from center beam on hemp rope"
BAÐSTOFA INTERIOR-POST-MEAL:
"Dark interior of 12x16 foot turf house, single whale oil lamp creating golden light pool with deep shadows beyond, blackened ceiling beams with sheep wool insulation visible between rafters, frost crystallizing on inner turf walls in fractal patterns, empty rope hanging from center beam"
BAÐSTOFA DAWN-REVELATION:
"Dim grey dawn light filtering through smoke hole into 12x16 foot turf house interior, no lamp lit, shadows blue-grey, frost on turf walls gleaming with moisture, wooden sleeping platforms visible with bundled shapes"
BEACH EXTERIOR-STORM:
"Black volcanic sand beach at Látrabjarg cliffs Westfjords Iceland, heavy snowfall with 40mph horizontal wind, grey-green rough sea with white foam and ice chunks grinding against shore, visibility under 50 feet"
NIGHT BLIZZARD-ENCOUNTER:
"Night blizzard in complete whiteout, visibility exactly 3 feet, snow particles frozen in air like static, all surfaces accumulating white, no visible ground or sky distinction"
AERIAL COSMIC-ABANDONMENT:
"5000-foot altitude above Westfjords at winter dawn, dying aurora borealis green ribbons dissipating, grey cloud layer below, frozen fjord visible through gaps showing 60% ice coverage"
UNDERWATER-EMPTY:
"Underwater beneath Arctic ocean surface, grey-green murk with visibility 10 feet, ice crystals drifting like snow, shafts of dim light from above"
COMPLETE CHARACTER ANCHORS WITH DETAILS
MAGNÚS-STANDARD:
"55-year-old Icelandic man with thick grey unkempt beard reaching chest, deep-set blue eyes with crow's feet, weathered face with broken capillaries on cheeks, wearing brown homespun wool sweater with visible mending"
MAGNÚS-DETERIORATING:
"55-year-old Icelandic man with thick grey unkempt beard matted with ice, bloodshot eyes with dilated pupils, weathered face gaunt from starvation, brown wool sweater hanging loose on thinning frame"
GUÐRÚN-STANDARD:
"35-year-old Icelandic woman wearing white curved faldbúningur headdress with black band, pale face with sharp cheekbones, brown wool dress with leather apron, hands chapped red from cold"
SIGRID-STANDARD:
"16-year-old girl with wheat-blonde braids reaching waist, grey eyes that never blink enough, angular face suggesting early womanhood, grey-brown patched dress too small for growing frame"
SIGRID-FEARFUL:
"16-year-old girl with wheat-blonde braids pulled tight, body language contracted, grey-brown patched dress pulled close, positioning herself behind furniture or in corners"
JÓN-STANDARD:
"8-year-old boy with sandy hair falling over eyes, freckles across nose, wearing oversized brown sweater with sleeves rolled up three times, thin legs in patched wool trousers"
LILJA-STANDARD:
"5-year-old girl with tangled dark blonde hair, large blue eyes too big for small face, grey wool dress dragging ground, constantly clutching cloth doll with brass button eyes"
ANIMAL ANCHORS WITH VARIATIONS
RAM-SUPERNATURAL:
"Massive Icelandic forystufé ram with thick white wool hanging in dreadlocks, black eyes reflecting light like mirrors, curved horns yellowed with age, standing completely still despite wind"
SHEEP-TRANSFORMED:
"Icelandic sheep with human-like positioning, white wool too clean for barn animals, breathing rhythm matching human sleep patterns, arranged by size on sleeping platforms"
SHEEP-INDIVIDUAL:
"Single Icelandic sheep with distinctive marker [headdress/sweater/doll], eyes closed in human-like sleep expression, wool rising and falling with deep breaths"
CRITICAL OBJECT ANCHORS
RITUAL ARRANGEMENT-COMPLETE:
"Cross pattern made from four white shark cartilage ribs with grey sheep wool wound between them on dark wooden table, small drops of blood on wool fibers, bone needle placed at center"
SHARK MEAT-HANGING:
"Grey-pink fermented shark meat piece size of human torso, surface crystallized with poisonous ammonia, dripping clear liquid into wooden bowl, hemp rope dark with absorbed fluids"
HEADDRESS-DISPLACED:
"White curved faldbúningur headdress with black velvet band and silver brooch, sitting wrongly on sheep's head between ears, tail piece dragging in straw"
CLOTH DOLL-CONSTANT:
"Six-inch cloth doll with grey wool body, brass military buttons for eyes, yarn hair made from unraveled sweater, one arm shorter than other"

COMPLETE SHOT LIST - 82 SHOTS TOTAL
Runtime: 12 minutes (720 seconds)
Coverage Requirements: Minimum 3 takes per shot

PROLOGUE: COSMIC ABANDONMENT (0:00-0:55)
SHOT_0 - VEO - AURORA DESCENT (12 sec)
Prompt: "Aerial view from 5000 feet above frozen Westfjords Iceland at dawn, dying green aurora borealis ribbons dissolving in grey sky, camera slowly descending through aurora remnants, through grey cloud layer, emerging above frozen fjord with 60% ice coverage, tiny black specks of structures below, no sound except high-altitude wind"
Technical Direction: Use slowest possible descent, hold on aurora dissolution for 4 seconds before descent begins
Purpose: Establish cosmic abandonment - the divine departing
Post: No music, only stratospheric wind
SHOT_1 - TEXT CARD (3 sec)
Prompt: "Pure black screen with centered white text in Helvetica: 'They will eat poison or starve. There is no third choice.'"
Purpose: State impossible decision explicitly
Post: Complete silence
SHOT_2 - RUNWAY - SHARK REVELATION (6 sec)
