COMPREHENSIVE PRODUCTION NOTES
Technical Specifications

Total Shots: 82
Total Runtime: 720 seconds (12 minutes)
Average Shot Length: 8.8 seconds
Longest Holds: Shot 37b (15 sec), Shot 50 (15 sec), Shot 58 (15 sec)
Shortest Cuts: Shot 21 (2 sec), Shot 29 (2 sec), Shot 30 (2 sec)
Coverage Ratio: 3:1 minimum, 5:1 for critical shots

Prompt Engineering Guidelines
Structure Every Prompt As:

Shot type/angle (Wide shot, Close-up, Aerial)
Primary subject with full description
Action/position if any
Environment with complete details
Lighting direction and quality
Atmosphere (particles, weather, etc.)
Technical notes (depth of field, motion, etc.)

Power Words for AI Generation:

Lighting: "Rembrandt lighting," "harsh shadows," "golden hour," "single source"
Atmosphere: "dust motes," "breath vapor," "crystalline," "particles"
Texture: "weathered," "rough-hewn," "crystallized," "matted"
Mood: "liminal," "uncanny," "suffocating," "vast"

Avoid These Terms:

Emotional descriptors ("sad," "angry," "desperate")
Complex interactions ("fighting," "arguing," "embracing")
Specific expressions ("smiling," "crying," "grimacing")
Abstract concepts ("poverty," "isolation," "tradition")

Sound Design Layers
Frequency Architecture:

Sub-40Hz: House foundation creaking (felt not heard)
70-90Hz: Trawler horn (industrial presence)
200-800Hz: Breathing ambiguity (human/animal)
1000-3000Hz: Wind through gaps (constant anxiety)
Above 8000Hz: Ice crystallizing (subtle terror)

Critical Sound Moments:

Shot 37b: 15-second hold needs evolving soundscape
Shot 38c: Complete silence for 4 seconds must feel wrong
Shot 57: Bleat-to-voice transformation is the film's audio climax
Shot 58b: Fade to absolute silence over final 6 seconds

Dialogue Placement (Magnús only speaks):

"Tíu...ellefu...nei..." (Shot 11 - counting confusion)
"You hide food while we starve!" (Shot 28b)
"Find seaweed. Don't return empty." (Shot 32)
"TAKE ME INSTEAD!" (Shot 22)
"Eat! Every piece!" (Shot 42)
"Guðrún? Where..." (Shot 47)
"Guðrún! JÓN!" (Shot 53)
"No... no..." (Shot 53b)
[Broken lullaby] (Shot 56)
"Einn... tveir... þrír..." (Shot 58)

The Three-Layer Reality Checklist
Each Act Must Contain:

Physical Evidence: Poisoned meat, dilated pupils, scratched bowls
Psychological Markers: Counting problems, perception breaks, shared behaviors
Supernatural Elements: Impossible physics, ritual components, transformations

Never Resolve Whether:

The sheep are transformed family OR dying family covered in wool
Magnús is hallucinating OR seeing truth
The ritual worked OR coincidence occurred
The ram was supernatural OR Magnús imagined it

Cultural Authenticity Markers
Must Include:

Hákarl: Fermented shark as actual survival food
Tilberi: Fragmentary folk magic for milk-stealing
Forystufé: Lead sheep with supernatural significance
Níðstöng: Curse poles against enemies
Faldbúningur: Specific Icelandic women's headdress
Morgundrengur: Morning confusion state
Sjávargalinn: Shark-poisoning madness

Must Avoid:

Generic "Viking" imagery
Modern Icelandic references
Christian overtones (use pagan/folk elements)
Contemporary speech patterns

Visual Motif Tracking
Cross Patterns:

Shot 2b: Empty drying rack
Shot 7b: Frost on window
Shot 9b: Crossed firewood
Shot 11c: Children's rib bones
Shot 14: Ritual arrangement
Shot 35: Sigrid's ritual

V-Notches (The Missing Ram):

Shot 2c: Wall counting marks
Shot 24: Seal flipper
Shot 39: Ram's ear

Black in White (Corruption):

Shot 10b: Black thread in white fabric
Shot 40: Coal rope in wool
Shot 43: Dilated pupils
Shot 50: Dark shapes in white wool

Extended Shot Strategies
To achieve 12-minute runtime with 82 shots:
Hold Discomfort:

Let silences extend past comfort
Static shots where only snow moves
Breathing as primary sound
No cutting during transformations

Use Tableau Staging:

Family positioned like paintings
Minimal movement within frames
Environmental motion only (smoke, snow)
Eyes tell story, not actions

Reality Breaks:

Physics violations subtle but present
Shadows wrong for light sources
Breath patterns not matching visible sources
Time seeming to skip or repeat

Final Assembly Notes
Pacing Structure:

Opening: Slow, cosmic (average 8 sec/shot)
Act I: Building tension (average 7 sec/shot)
Boat/Violence: Quick cuts (average 6 sec/shot)
Night Journey: Extended holds (average 10 sec/shot)
Revelation: Painfully slow (average 12 sec/shot)

The Film's Core Question:
Not "What happened?" but "What does it mean that we cannot know what happened?"
The Three Endings Simultaneously True:

Realistic: Family dead under wool, Magnús poisoned/insane
Psychological: Shared delusion from isolation/starvation
Supernatural: Tilberi magic transformed them

All three exist in quantum superposition. The film collapses into meaning only in each viewer's mind.

FINAL WORD: This film succeeds if audiences leave arguing not about what they saw, but about what reality itself means when survival strips away certainty. The horror isn't the sheep—it's the impossibility of knowing if there are sheep at all.
END OF COMPLETE PRODUCTION BIBLE v2.0
Total Shots: 82
Runtime: 12 minutes
Coverage: 3:1 minimum
Aspect Ratio: 2.39:1 (Cinemascope for maximum isolation)
Color: Desaturated except lamp light (amber) and blood (red)